text.p: An earthquake shook Israel on Wednesday, but there were no immediate reports of injuries or damage, Israel's Itim news agency said.

The tremor, whose magnitude was not immediately available, was felt at 1314 GMT in Tel Aviv, Jerusalem and the West Bank town of Ramallah, witnesses said. Furniture shook in the Reuters bureau in downtown Jerusalem.
A Reuters correspondent in Tel Aviv described the tremor felt there as powerful.
"They evacuated the whole building. The floors shook," she said by mobile telephone outside the Reuters office in Tel Aviv.
Palestinians in Gaza said they also felt the tremor.
Officials at Israel's seismology institute were not immediately available to comment.
